## 🏁 Deployment Test

Unplug your mouse and all temporary configuration peripherals. Leave only the monitor and a keyboard connected, then run the reboot command:

```bash
sudo reboot

```

**The Final Result:** Your Raspberry Pi will boot up cleanly with minimal scrolling text, skip the password login prompt entirely, and within seconds, your display will snap into a 100% full-screen slideshow presentation. It will seamlessly cycle through all images in your folder every 5 seconds infinitely!

