## 💡 Slideshow Maintenance Tips

* **How do I adjust the image rotation speed (staying time)?**
Open your `/home/user/.bashrc` file, go to the bottom, and modify the `-t 5` flag in the `fbi` command. For example, `-t 10` means each image stays for 10 seconds, while `-t 30` sets it to half a minute.
* **How do I update, add, or delete advertising images later?**
You can connect to the Pi via SSH or FileZilla anytime while the machine is running and drop new photos into or delete old ones from `/home/user/images/`. Once done, simply run `sudo reboot` to apply changes.
* **How do I exit the loop to access the command line locally?**
Connect a physical keyboard to the Pi and tap the **`Q` key** or the **`Esc` key**. The `fbi` loop instance will terminate safely, dropping you right back to your regular `user@display1:~ $` prompt.
